Detailed Description

Interface for DFRobot's Power Shield (SKU:DFR0105).

See also:
http://www.dfrobot.com/wiki/index.php/Power_Shield_(SKU:DFR0105) for hardware details.

By default, the auxiliary ower output is disabled (see implementation of DFRobotPowerShield::init() ).

void DFRobotPowerShield::setVoltageRange ( float  argMin,
float  argMax 
)

DFRobotPowerShield::setVoltageRange To modify the voltage range measured by AN0; as the auxyliary output's voltage is measured through a pont diviseur de tension, the exact value may vary depending on the resistors.

Use this method to adjust the min/max to best fit to the board.

Parameters:
argMin The voltage of the auxiliary output when AN0 value is 0/1024.
argMax The voltage of the auxiliary output when AN0 value is 1024/1024.
